==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extraterritoriality
<hw>Ex`tra*ter`ri*to`ri*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The state of being beyond the limits of a particular
territory</def>; esp. <fld>(Internat. Law)</fld>, <def>A fiction by
which a public minister, though actually in a foreign country, is
supposed still to remain within the territory of his own sovereign or
nation.</def> <rj><au>Wheaton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extratropical</ent>⟦br⟧
